elsh  ,   Walsh  . The idea that the Scottish surname refers to the Welsh-speaking Britons of Strathclyde is erroneous."]}]},{"name":"Aymer","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Great and noble"],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Bright’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Aymer de Wallace was born in 1090, in Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, Sir Galeius Walense Le'Strange, was 22 and his mother, Gennavieve Le'Wallense, was 35. He married Lady Eimerus de Wallense in 1115, in Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1181, in Clackmannan, Clackmannanshire, Scotland, at the age of 91."},"et":{"1090–1181":"1090–1181","1090–1185":"1090–1185","1100–1140":"1100–1140","–Female":"Surnud","1095–Female":"1095–Surnud","1117–1180":"1117–1180","1068–1118":"1068–1118","1055–1118":"1055–1118","1090":"1090","1088":"1088","1055":"1055","1185":"1185","1140":"1140","1095":"1095","1181":"1181","1180":"1180","1118":"1118","1117":"1117","1115":"1115","1068":"1068","1100":"1100","Riccarton Castle, Paisley, Renfrew, Scotland":"Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland","Clackmannan, Clackmannanshire, Scotland":"Clackmannan, Clackmannanshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1090–1181":"1090–1181","1090–1185":"1090–1185","1100–1140":"1100–1140","–Female":"Kuollut","1095–Female":"1095–Kuollut","1117–1180":"1117–1180","1068–1118":"1068–1118","1055–1118":"1055–1118","1090":"1090","1088":"1088","1055":"1055","1185":"1185","1140":"1140","1095":"1095","1181":"1181","1180":"1180","1118":"1118","1117":"1117","1115":"1115","1068":"1068","1100":"1100","Riccarton Castle, Paisley, Renfrew, Scotland":"Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland","Clackmannan, Clackmannanshire, Scotland":"Clackmannan, Clackmannanshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Ayrshire, Scotland":"Ayrshire, Skotlanti, Yhdi